source: tests/test_help.rs
expression: "normalize_output(&output, temp_dir.path(), &date)?"
---
$ govctl loop --help
Loop execution-state commands

Usage: govctl loop [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  list    List persisted local loop states
  start   Start a loop for one or more explicit work items
  show    Show persisted loop state
  resume  Resume or inspect an existing non-terminal loop
  replan  Recompute dependency closure for the current root set
  add     Add root work items to an existing loop and replan
  remove  Remove root work items from an existing loop and replan
  run     Run one execution round for each currently executable work item
  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -C, --config <CONFIG>  Path to govctl config (TOML)
      --dry-run          Dry run: preview changes without writing files
  -h, --help             Print help

COMMON WORKFLOW:
    1. `govctl loop list open` to discover existing non-terminal loops
    2. `govctl loop start WI-<DATE>-001` to create local loop state
    3. `govctl loop run --id <LOOP-ID>` to execute one round for ready work
    4. `govctl loop show <LOOP-ID>` to inspect persisted state
    5. `govctl loop resume --id <LOOP-ID>` to resume discovered loop state
    6. `govctl loop add --id <LOOP-ID> WI-<DATE>-002` to expand scope

NOTES:
    - Loop state is local under `.govctl/loops/<LOOP-ID>/state.toml`.
    - Use `loop list open` before guessing a loop ID or root set after interruption.
    - `loop run` uses work-item lifecycle commands for status transitions.
exit: 0
